weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new 
roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>just</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:706px;top:126px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new 
roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>confidential</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:805px;top:126px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new 
roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>in</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:824px;top:126px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new 
roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>compliance </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:373px;top:148px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new 
roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>with the regulations that apply to any 
publicly traded company</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:248px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>In 
Section 15, the Law establishes that for the execution of the&nbsp; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:270px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-
serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>Company&#146;s activities, YPF &#147;<b>shall continue to 
operate as a public </b></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:291px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:bold;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>company 
pursuant to Chapter II, Section V of Law N&#186; 19,550 and&nbsp; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:312px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:bold;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>its 
corresponding regulations<b></b><font size='3.8' face='arial,sans-serif' 
color='#FFFFFF'>, and
shall not be subject to any</font><b></b><font size='3.8' face='arial,sans-
serif' color='#FFFFFF'> </font></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:334px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-
serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>legislation or regulation applicable to the management or 
control of </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:355px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-
serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>Companies or entities owned by the National Government or 
</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:376px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#FFFFFF;'> 
provincial governments&#148;.&nbsp; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:404px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:bold;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>YPF is 
not a state&#45;owned company,
<b></b><font size='3.8' face='arial,sans-serif' 
color='#FFFFFF'>bu</font><b></b><font size='3.8' face='arial,sans-serif' 
color='#FFFFFF'>t, as stated in the Law, is a </font></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:429px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-
serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>corporation. For that reason, negotiations with Chevron 
were carried&nbsp; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:453px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>out in
compliance with all <b>obligations arising from both the </b></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:478px;font-style:normal;font-
weight:bold;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-

and </div>

Buenos Aires and New York </font></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:371px;top:527px;font-style:normal;font-
